'''''Space Battle''''' (also known as '''''Space Battles''''')<ref name=":0" /> is a 1978 video game developed by [[Level IV Products|Level IV]] for the [[TRS-80]] 16K Level II microcomputer.

==Gameplay==
''Space Battle'' is a ''[[Star Trek (1971 video game)|Star Trek]]''-style game, in which the player take the role of a mercenary ship engaged in combat with hostile alien ships.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
In ''80-US'', Geo Blank compared the game to ''[[Time Trek]]'', and rated its content "Excellent" and its value "Good to very good", concluding that it was "One of the best space war games available."<ref name="Blank1980">{{cite magazine |last=Blank |first=Geo |date=March–April 1980 |title=Space Battle |url=https://archive.org/details/80-U.S._Volume_III_Number_2_1980-03_80-Northwest_Publishing_US/page/n70 |magazine=80-U.S. |publisher=80-Northwest Publishing Co. |location=Tacoma, WA |volume=3 |issue=2 |page=69 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}</ref> J. Mishcon reviewed ''Space Battle'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 28, commenting that "I believe most gamer will set this aside - a nice try, but not really a challenge. The tactics are just too easily optimized."<ref name="SG">{{cite magazine |last=Mishcon |first=J. |date=May–June 1980 |title=Space Battle |url=https://archive.org/stream/space-gamer_201601/Space_Gamer_28#page/n25/ |magazine=[[The Space Gamer]] |publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]] |issue=28 |department=Capsule Reviews |pages=25–26 |issn=0194-9977 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}</ref> In ''[[Moves (magazine)|Moves]]'', the game was criticised for not holding long-term interest compared to other similar games.<ref name=":0">{{Cite magazine |date=February–March 1981 |title=Space Battles |url=https://strategyandtacticspress.com/library-files/Moves%20Issue55.pdf |magazine=[[Moves (magazine)|Moves]] |issue=55 |page=32 |access-date=14 July 2023}}</ref>

